# Create a .secrets file with your Docker Hub credentials
# Format: KEY=VALUE (one per line)
# 
# Example:
# DOCKERHUB_USERNAME=your_dockerhub_username
# DOCKERHUB_TOKEN=your_dockerhub_personal_access_token
# SECRET_KEY_BASE=your_secret_key_base_for_elixir
#
# To get a Docker Hub token:
# 1. Go to https://hub.docker.com/settings/security
# 2. Click 'New Access Token'
# 3. Give it a name like 'GitHub Actions'
# 4. Copy the token (starts with 'dckr_pat_')
#
# For SECRET_KEY_BASE, you can generate one with:
# mix phx.gen.secret
